<font class=FieldValue>
<p>Every light casts at least one shadow, and within these shadows one can almost always find the Cathari observing 
silently. Their motives never clear, their actions never obvious, their thoughts always towards the future... 
This secrecy houses their power.  The Illumin Cathari have learned it is best to rule from the shadows than to burn in 
the light.</p>
<p>While the guild is focused around the whole of the team; individualism is highly encouraged. It is for this reason 
that members are carefully chosen; recruits generally show self-sufficient traits and the ability to listen to their own 
instinct and deal with adversity in a calm and collected manor. While our actions and existence may be looked down upon by 
other groups; never will we need to prey upon the weak, or kill out of petty jealousy or spite.</p>
